article.headline: Emanuel scores 29 points, Fairleigh Dickinson secures 81-74 OT victory over Stonehill
article.description: — Jo'el Emanuel had 29 points, including nine in overtime, in Fairleigh Dickinson's 81-74 win against Stonehill on Saturday.
article.linkText: Emanuel scores 29 points, Fairleigh Dickinson secures 81-74 OT victory over Stonehill
article.story: TEANECK, N.J. -- — Jo'el Emanuel had 29 points, including nine in overtime, in Fairleigh Dickinson's 81-74 win against Stonehill on Saturday. Emanuel added seven rebounds for the Knights (7-11, 1-2 Northeast Conference). Terrence Brown shot 5 for 9 (3 for 4 from 3-point range) and 2 of 3 from the free throw line to add 15 points. Ansley Almonor had 11 points and was 2 of 8 shooting, including 2 for 6 from 3-point range, and went 5 for 5 from the line. The Knights broke a six-game losing streak. Tony Felder led the Skyhawks (2-16, 0-3) in scoring, finishing with 18 points and two steals. Jackson Benigni added 16 points, six rebounds and two steals for Stonehill. Max Zegarowski also had 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
